---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Terms of Use — TextWizard';
const description =
  'Terms of use for TextWizard — free, open-source, MIT-licensed browser tools, provided as-is with no warranty.';
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="container legal">
    <p><a href="/" class="legal-back">← Back to TextWizard</a></p>
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: 2026-07-16</p>

    <p>By using TextWizard (the "Service"), you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, please don't use it.</p>

    <h2>What TextWizard is</h2>
    <p>
      TextWizard is a free collection of text and code tools that run entirely in your browser.
      There are no accounts, and the text you enter is processed locally on your device — see the
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is provided "as is" and "as available", without warranty of any kind, express or
      implied, including but not limited to merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
      non-infringement. We don't guarantee the tools are accurate, error-free, or available at any
      given time. Always verify important results yourself.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, the authors and contributors are not liable for any
      damages or losses arising from your use of — or inability to use — the Service, including any
      loss of data.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
      Don't use TextWizard for anything unlawful, and don't attempt to disrupt or abuse the site or
      the infrastructure that serves it. The tools run in your browser; you are responsible for the
      content you process with them and for complying with any laws that apply to it.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content</h2>
    <p>
      You keep all rights to the text and files you use with the tools. Because everything runs
      locally, we never receive, store, or claim any rights to your content.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      The site is hosted on Cloudflare and uses self-hosted, cookieless Plausible analytics for
      aggregate page-view counts. Their handling of basic request metadata is described in the
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Open source &amp; license</h2>
    <p>
      TextWizard is open source under the MIT License — you're free to use, modify, and redistribute
      the code under those terms. The source is on
      <a href="https://github.com/MichalAFerber/textwizard" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms; the "Last updated" date above will change. Continued use after an
      update means you accept the revised terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions? Reach us via <a href="/contact">Contact</a>.</p>
  </main>
</Base>
